    <ReasonableCauseExplanation documentId="RetDoc2125800001">
      <ExplanationTxt>THE FOUNDATION WAS RECENTLY GRANTED EXEMPT STATUS AS A SUPPORT ORGANIZATION UNDER INTERNAL REVENUE CODE SECTION 509(A)(3). WHEN THE ORGANIZATION RECEIVED THE APPROVAL LETTER, THE INITIAL FISCAL YEAR WAS ALREADY COMPLETED. THERE WAS NO ACTIVITY FOR THE YEAR ENDED JUNE 30, 2018. THE APPROVAL LETTER STATED THAT THE ORGANIZATION WAS REQUIRED TO FILE FORM 990, 990-EZ OR 990-N. SINCE THERE WAS NO ACTIVITY, THE ORGANIZATION REQUESTED THAT GOFF BACKA ALFERA &amp; COMPANY (CPA FIRM) FILE FORM 990-N ON THEIR BEHALF. BASED ON FURTHER RESEARCH, THE OUR FIRM DETERMINED THAT A 990-N COULD NOT BE FILED FOR SUPPORTING ORGANIZATION. FORM 990-EZ WAS NOT EXTENDED SO THE RETURN IS LATE. WE ARE REQUESTING THAT PENALTIES FOR LATE FILING BE WAIVED DUE TO REASONABLE CAUSE. THE ORGANIZATION WILL BE TIMELY FILING FORM 990-EZ FOR ALL FUTURE YEARS.</ExplanationTxt>
